## Voltara

**The problem**
For my Web Technologies semester project at university, I had to build a complete full-stack web application from scratch, not a toy demo, something that actually behaved like a real product: user accounts, an admin side, a working catalogue, all of it.

**What I did**
I built Voltara, a full-stack site for a fictional solar energy company, on Node.js, Express, and MongoDB, with EJS handling the templating. I put in proper user authentication with bcrypt password hashing and session management, and role-based access so admins get a full management panel while customers just see the shop. The product catalogue handles 28 products with category filtering and server-side pagination, and I added a dynamic on-sale page that paginates client-side with jQuery, so browsing sale items doesn't reload the page. The homepage has a quote request form with live validation on name, phone, and email, and the whole thing is responsive on mobile via Bootstrap 5.

**What came of it**
A working, end-to-end site with real CRUD in the admin panel, not just a front-end mockup. It's the project where I properly learned how the pieces of a full-stack app (auth, sessions, database, templating, client-side interactivity) actually fit together.

